1597	\section{Application: codim-1 extension on a regular surface (gating A.4.a)}
1598	\label{sec:ab_application_to_a4a}
1599	
1600	The downstream consumer is A.4.a: extending a rational map
1601	\(f : S \dashrightarrow A\) from a regular projective surface \(S\) to an abelian variety \(A\)
1602	across a closed point \(x \in S\) that is missing from the domain of definition \(U \subseteq S\).
1603	The classical mechanism (cf.\ Hartshorne, \emph{Algebraic Geometry}, III.7) is:
1604	
1605	\begin{enumerate}
1606	  \item The local ring \(\mathcal{O}_{S,x}\) is a regular Noetherian local ring of Krull
1607	    dimension \(2\) (because \(S\) is regular and \(\dim S = 2\)).
1608	  \item By \cref{cor:regular_cohen_macaulay} it is Cohen--Macaulay, so
1609	    \(\text{depth}(\mathcal{O}_{S,x}) = 2\). Equivalently, the maximal ideal contains an
1610	    \(\mathcal{O}_{S,x}\)-regular sequence of length \(2\) (any two transverse generators).
1611	  \item Sections of the structure sheaf \(\mathcal{O}_S\) on \(U = S \setminus \{x\}\) extend
1612	    uniquely across \(x\) because \(H^0_x(\mathcal{O}_S) = 0\) and
1613	    \(H^1_x(\mathcal{O}_S) = 0\) (these local-cohomology vanishings are equivalent to depth
1614	    \(\geq 2\) at \(x\) by Stacks tag 0AVF; see Hartshorne, III.3.5, for the surface case).
1615	  \item For a rational map \(f : S \dashrightarrow A\) with codimension-\(\geq 2\) indeterminacy
1616	    locus on a regular surface, the same depth-\(\geq 2\) input produces a sheaf-theoretic
1617	    extension of \(f\) to all of \(S\): pull back any sheaf \(\mathcal{O}_A\)-affine-locally,
1618	    obtain sections over \(U\), and extend across \(x\) by the above.
1619	\end{enumerate}
1620	
1621	So \cref{cor:regular_cohen_macaulay} is the gating input: the geometric A.4.a
1622	proof can be written conditional on the algebraic Auslander--Buchsbaum corollary, and the
1623	two halves develop independently --- as long as \cref{thm:auslander_buchsbaum} and
1624	\cref{cor:regular_cohen_macaulay} are formalized in
1625	\texttt{AlgebraicJacobian/Albanese/AuslanderBuchsbaum.lean} with the signatures pinned
1626	in this chapter, A.4.a can consume them as Mathlib-style imports.
1627	
